		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.03]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gbaji&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p><blockquote><b class="sm">Gladestrider wrote:</b><hr size="1" />I tried the GY at Katta with my rogue just after it became a hotzone (what an F'ing waste making Katta a hotzone...). It wasn't bad exp, and I went from 46-47. The annoying part was that you have to run all over the GY to get the mobs to spawn, and you occasionally get 2 or 3 that spawn in close proximity, at the same time. I would think that it would be pretty slow for a 51, since you'd have to be able to constantly kill to make it worthwhile.<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br /><br />IVU is your friend in the Katta GY (that's invisibility versus undead in case you're wondering).<br /><br />What actually spawns in the graveyard are invisible &quot;traps&quot;, which when you walk near them cause an undead mob to appear. If you run around with IVU up, you'll trigger the traps, but the undead wont agro on you (cause you're invisible to them, right?).<br /><br />What I did back in the day was run a circut through the GY with IVU up until I got an undead to appear. I then ran back to the building there and used a spell to pull the mob to me. The mobs don't trigger the traps, so there's no danger of getting an add while pulling that way. If you agro a mob and run somewhere else, there's always a chance that you'll trigger another trap and get two mobs on you.<br /><br />Using that method is pretty much completely safe.<br /><br /><br />Killing the taskmaster in EC is super easy as well. The skeletons don't assist him, so you don't actually have to pacify them to pull the TM. What I did was fear him instead of tank him (cause his damage was a touch nasty at the level it's worth hunting there). When feared, he'll run down the tunnels and all the way to the SH zoneline. He'll then stand there against the zoneline with his back to you while you beat on him and finish him off. Just keep applying fear as you chase him through the zone and you'll be fine. It's a good idea to clear the other mobs along the way as well (only have to clear like 3 to be able to safely move out of there). Some might say it's an exploit to kill him this way, but I don't agree. Clearly, fear kiting is allowed in the game, and it's not my fault that the mob runs to a spot where he'll get &quot;stuck&quot;. You do have to be careful to not move to close behind him though, or you'll accidentally zone.<br /><br />It's worth doing if for no other reason then the EB item you'll get if you can collect 4 of the undead shissar organs.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from San Diego, CA</td></tr></table>
