		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.03]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gbaji&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p><blockquote><b class="sm">czaemon wrote:</b><hr size="1" /><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />Enjoy your undead hunting now while you can. Post 60, there's virtually no undead worth mentioning in the game. SoE, in its infinite wisdom, hasn't actually provided any worthwhile undead &quot;camps&quot; since the Luclin expansion. All undead in PoP, OoW, and GoD are randomly placed in among live mobs, so you're pretty much screwed later on... <hr size="1" /></blockquote><br />codecay has a load of undead.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br />time has two trials that are 100% undead, and some other undead scattered throughout. <hr size="1" /></blockquote><br /><br />Can't speak for Time since I've not been there. But CoD is *not* full of undead.<br /><br />See. You'd think it would be. And I thought it would be too. But after spending a ridiculous amount of time helping out a couple shamans get their 1.5 bit there, I can say with absolute clarity that fewer then 50% of the mobs <b>even at the &quot;undead&quot; camps</b> are actually undead mobs. They may look like they should be undead. They may have names that imply they are undead, but they are not, in fact, undead mobs...<br /><br />Look <a href="HTTP://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?zone=174" target="akztarg">here</a>.<br /><br />There are only five actual undead mob types in the entire zone: &quot;A corpse scavenger&quot;, &quot;Elite corrupted knight&quot;, &quot;Elite death knight&quot;, &quot;Knight of decay&quot;, and &quot;Reanimated reaver&quot;.<br /><br />Interestingly enough, other mobs that seem really similar, or are in the same areas are *not* undead like: &quot;Death knight&quot;, &quot;Corrupted knight&quot;, &quot;Elite knight of decay&quot;, &quot;Elite necromancer of decay&quot;, &quot;magus of decay&quot;, etc...<br /><br /><br />It's a common misconception that there are more undead mobs in a given zone/camp/area then there actually are. I'm extremely well attuned to the actual rates of undead mobs because I make an assessment as to whether to use my &quot;normal&quot; proc spell or my undead proc spell on my paladin all the time. The normal one does half the damage but affects all mobs and the undead only one does twice the damage but affects only undead. There are virtually zero camps in the game where it's actually worth using the undead-only version since they almost all will involve killing 50% or more live mobs just to keep the camp clear.<br /><br />Same exact deal with CoD. I thought as you did that there were lots of undead there. People who'd hunted there before were *sure* that there were mostly undead in the zone (and especially where we were camping). So I loaded up the anti-undead proc, and found to my dismay that something like 80% of the mobs got me a nice fat &quot;this spell only affects undead&quot; message.<br /><br />I've bitched about this in the past, and I'll bitch about it again. There is a *huge* misconception about the availability of undead camps in the game. Since Luclin, SoE primarily uses undead mobs purely as a way to make it harder for folks to invis past content. They scatter undead mobs around for variety. There are almost no actual undead-only camps though.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from San Diego, CA</td></tr></table>
