		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1286"><span id=Encyclopedia>gbaji</span></a><b><span id=Encyclopedia><br>Encyclopedia</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />9923 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.03]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gbaji&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p><blockquote><b class="sm">jpstarcher wrote:</b><hr size="1" /><br />I dont know what creatures you refer to.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have killed restless souls , cragwalkers, hynids, stonemites, reef crustaceans, and potameids for about a year.  So far, only restless souls are KOS.  the &quot;creatures of taelosia&quot; faction lists hynids and reef crustaceans as being on this faction, but I have never seen a faction hit when killing them.  I kill hynids 4 at a time, and when they are gone, take out the cragwalkers, then pull a few restless ones until hynids pop again.<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br /><br />I was killing restless soul's just a week ago. I saw the faction hit for Creatures of Talsosia message when I killed one. That caused me to check to see what was on it.<br /><br />How many restless souls have you actually killed? See. I've killed the other creatures as well and never seen the message either. It would not be the first time that SoE has put in a faction like this where killing the mobs on the faction doesn't actually cause a faction hit, but killing other mobs does affect that faction.<br /><br />In most cases this is done in a sensical and useful manner. For example. Once you kill enough giants in Velious to be non-kos to CoV faction, you can travel to CS and the wyverns aren't KoS to you anymore. You can kill them all day long and take no faction hits, making for a nice bit of camping.<br /><br />It looks to me like they did this one in a similar way. The creatures (hynids, cragwalkers, stonemites) are all on the faction but dont generate any faction hit when you kill them. Killing the restless souls *will* affect faction with them.<br /><br />There's a few possiblities (since I've not heard anything from anyone else on this, and there's nothing posted about this faction here):<br /><br />1. They only recently added the faction hit (Honestly, I could have sworn I was killing some about a month ago and I didn't see or remember a faction hit, but killing one a week ago did have one). If that's the case, then all that killing you did in the past didn't matter.<br /><br />2. You just never noticed the hit, and never killed enough to make you KoS. Again. It's entirely possible that only the restless souls generate a negative faction hit, while killing the creatures themselves does not.<br /><br />3. The default faction for most of those creatures is high enough and the range narrow enough that they wont go KoS even if you go max negative (except for the restless souls themselves). It's possible for this to be true. And if it is, I'd actually *love* it, since that would make this a viable camp. I have to wonder if that's really the case though. Why bother putting in a faction hit if the undead you're killing already start out KoS, and everything else on the faction can't go KoS no matter how bad the faction? Why not just leave it out? I have to assume that if I'm taking a negative faction hit, that at some point that means I'll go KoS to mobs on that faction. Otherwise, why have the faction in the first place?<br /><br /><br />Again. I've not heard or know enough to be sure. If you can absolutely verify that no amount of killing there will make you KoS with any of the mobs on that faction, I'd love to know that for sure. I just have to wonder what the point of the faction is if that's the case though. The one thing I know for absolutely 100% sure is that as of about 1 week ago, killing restless souls in Natimbi did generate a faction hit for Creatures of Talosia.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from San Diego, CA</td></tr></table>
